column18:
[['1.  Interval placement of an endotracheal tube which has its tip approximately 4.5 cm above the carina.  Interval placement of a nasogastric tube which has its tip coursing below the diaphragm, although the tip is not clearly identified.  There is a persistent but improving left retrocardiac airspace process, which may be due to compressive atelectasis, although aspiration or pneumonia should also be considered.  There is likely a layering left effusion, although the effusion is difficult to quantify on a semi-upright radiograph.  No evidence of pulmonary edema.  No pneumothorax.  Overall cardiac and mediastinal contours are stable.'
  None]]
column20:
[['Moderate cardiomegaly with mild pulmonary vascular congestion and small bilateral pleural effusions.'
  None]]

column23:

  None]]
column24:
